  <prompt>
    Build selective recall via embedding similarity. At write time, vectorize each chat
    turn (or compressed summary) using the existing `IEmbeddingCache` infrastructure;
    persist vector alongside the turn metadata in Cosmos `sessions`. At read time
    (during prompt assembly in `PlaybookChatContextProvider`), when the current question
    relates to old turns beyond the recent verbatim window, retrieve top-K (e.g., 3-5)
    most similar old turns by cosine similarity. Respects token budget (NFR-10) — recall
    capped so total prompt stays ≤8K. Per-tenant isolation via partition key.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior AI platform engineer with experience in embedding-based retrieval +
    vector similarity + token budget management.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Selective recall implemented; vectorize at write; retrieve top-K by similarity at
    read; budget capped; per-tenant isolated.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="project-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-plan">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/plan.md</file>
